threads.title: 820 00165 not turning on
threads.message:
I have a macbook air with this main board 820-00165. Laptop was liquid damaged. It is not turning on. Green and orange charger light is present.
Fan spin for about 1 second then stop.

PPBUS_G3H 8.63v
PPDCIN_G3H_ISOL 15v
PPDCIN_G3H 14.43v
PP3V42_G3H 3.45v
PPVRTC_G3H 3.33v
PP5V_S5 5.5v
PP5V_S4RS3 0v
PM_SLP_S4_L 0v
PP5V_S0 0v
SMC_BC_ACOK 3.42v
PP3V3_S5 3.33
PM_BATLOW_L 3.33v
PM_SLP_SUS_L 3.33v
SMC_ADAPTER_EN 3.44v
PPVCC_S0_CPU 0v
u6100 3.33v


thanks

threads.title: 820 00165 not turning on
threads.message: water damage around U6100 and/or J6100.........

threads.title: 820 00165 not turning on
threads.message: Check for power pulsing at PP5V_S4RS3, best to use scope as pulses are hard to catch on multimeter. And of course check for corrosions U6100 and the termination resistors/traces and U1950 pin 8.
